<span id="freeTextContainer16625390044160823169">Nothing but pure delight -- entertainment at its best, with a few life lessons thrown in, for good measure. <br/><br/>Joanne Harris novels never fail to put me in a good mood, just through the sheer delight of her writing. Sometimes you just need to smile, and be entertained. Sometimes you just need a good game of (psychological) chess to chase away the cobwebs of winter. This delivers on both counts.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


